text: fixation_VTI() function operates differently fixation_dispersion(). determines fixations assessing velocity eye-movements, using method similar proposed Salvucci & Goldberg (1996). applies algorithm used VTI_saccade() (detailed ) removes identified saccades assessing whether separated fixations outside dispersion tolerance. outside tolerance, fixation treated new fixation regardless length saccade separating . Compared fixation_dispersion(), fixation_VTI() conservative determining fixation smaller saccades discounted resulting data treated continued fixation (assuming within pixel tolerance set disp_tol). simple terms, fixation_VTI() calculates saccades within data identifies fixations (essentially) non-saccade periods. avoid eye gaze drift, applies dispersion tolerance parameter well ensure fixations can appropriately localised x,y coordinate pair. One current limitation fixation_VTI() present fixation_dispersion() need data complete NAs present, otherwise compute saccades. fixation_VTI() works best unsmoothed data (default settings), smoothing process alters velocity eye movement. working smoothed data, lowering default threshold parameter recommended “jerky” saccadic starts less sudden entry point saccade sooner.
